    <h1>Dental savings plans for the self-employed</h1>
    <p class="lead">When you work for yourself, there is no group dental plan behind you. A savings plan is a simple, low-cost way to keep dental care affordable without buying a full individual insurance policy.</p>
    <div class="verdict">
      <h4>The honest verdict</h4>
      <p>For freelancers, gig workers, and business owners, a savings plan is a practical, low-commitment option. It costs $100 to $200 a year, works immediately with no waiting period, has no annual cap, and requires no employer. If you expect a lot of covered routine care or want an insurer to share big costs, an individual PPO is worth comparing, and you can stack a savings plan on top later.</p>
    </div>
