    <div class="section-head"><span class="eyebrow">The self-employed gap</span><h2>No employer, no group plan</h2></div>
    <div class="grid-3">
      <div class="card"><span class="k">1</span><h3>You are on your own</h3><p>About 27 percent of US adults have no dental insurance, and the self-employed are heavily represented, because there is no group plan to join.</p></div>
      <div class="card"><span class="k">2</span><h3>Individual insurance adds up</h3><p>A standalone dental policy can run $240 to $600 a year with waiting periods and an annual cap. A savings plan is usually a fraction of that.</p></div>
      <div class="card"><span class="k">3</span><h3>Simple and flexible</h3><p>No claims, no employer paperwork, and you can cancel or stack it whenever your situation changes.</p></div>
